description.narrative: (Kenya): The Afya Jijini activity strengthens health systems and improves family planning, reproductive, maternal, newborn, child, and adolescent health in Nairobi County. Major activities include support to voluntary family planning; postnatal care; promotion of healthy spacing of births; emergency obstetric and newborn care; antenatal care; postnatal care for mother and newborn; prevention and case management of diarrhea and pneumonia at facility and community levels; routine immunization; and maternal nutrition. The activity will train health facility and community health volunteers to increase technical capacity; strengthen health information and supply chain systems for essential medical commodities; and enhance monitoring and supervision systems. These core interventions are vital as Afya Jijini focuses on select informal settlements of Nairobi County with some of the greatest health needs. Utilizing a health systems strengthening approach is a key element to ensure sustainability upon activity completion, which is vital to achieving the Kenya Integrated Country Strategy Goal 3 and the U.S. Department of State and USAID Joint Strategic Plan 2018-2022 objective 2.2 "promote healthy, educated, and productive populations in partner countries to drive inclusive and sustainable development, open new markets, and support U.S. prosperity and security objectives." Improving global public health supports the Administration's priority of asserting U.S. leadership and influence..
